r>
<br>
Many Warriors with EB weapons have indicated that it doesn't get them instant aggro.  They have to beat on the mob a while and get a lucky proc or two.  The only real difference between this and something like Willsapper is the amount of hate generated on a lucky proc and perhaps the proc rate.  Nothing more.<br>
<br>
It does not in any way shape or form close the instant aggro gap between Knights and Warriors.  It does not do what is being claimed it does.  Does it work better than other proc weapons?  I can but assume that it does.  Does it make relying on procs reliable and predictable?  No it does not.<br>
<br>
Now, if an EB weapon gave you a hot button you could press whenever you felt the need and it proced on command, I'd agree that it closed the instant aggro gap nicely and recommend that they make EB weapons more available.  It doesn't work that way though.<br>
<br>
And consider, how many 100HP pieces of gear are spread around in a typical high end guild compared to the number of EB weapons?  Ya think maybe there are a few more pieces of armor available than EB weapons?  Good bet.   So even if we accepted that EB weapons closed the instant aggro gap, as it is clear they do not, they still would not be as available and as numerous as those items that close the HP gap between Knights and Warriors.<br>
<br>
And it would still beg the question why a level 55 Paladin in crap gear should out instant aggro control a level 65 Warrior in the best gear the game offers and with over 100 AAXP, when a level 55 Warrior in crap gear will in no way shape or form out tank a level 65 Paladin in the best gear the game offers with over 100 AAXP.<br>
<br>
There is a basic inequity involved.  Knights can gain on or surpass a Warrior in all the significant ways a Warrior as a class is supposed to have advantages if the Knight has gear and AAXP the Warrior doesn't.  While there is no way the Warrior can gain on or surpass the Knight in all the significant ways a Knight as a class is supposed to have advantages, regardless of the Warrior's gear or AAXP.<br>
<br>
<br>
