<br>
For example it's not unusual to see something like<br>
<br>
proc EB<br>
Wizard cast SoS<br>
Wizard gets summoned<br>
<br>
Actually, even if the wizard didn't get summoned, usually a heavy nuker just decides to nuke even harder until he's summoned anyway.  At any rate, in this case Taunt is your most reliable friend (or maybe root).<br>
<br>
One EB weapon, in particular, is very ineffective against slow aggro, the most common kind of aggro management problem encountered.  You only have about 10 seconds between the time a Shaman lands Malo(s) and then Turgur.  It's even worse against Tash + Slow when dealing with an enchanter, to the point that I usually just rely on Taunt instead and bank the EB weapon for something that does more damage. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=apothesdrudoll>Apothes Drudoll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/03 1:54:58 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Knights and SK's getting chosen over warriors in exp gro</span><hr size=1> Btw Knights do not have INSTANT aggro as you claim. it does tak 2 to 5 seconds to cast stuns deopending on wich you use and it take at least 2 stuns to overcome tash and slow. Mind you it is a LOT faster aggro then a EB weapon but it is not instant as you say. The taunt button when it works is instant aggro unlike spell aggro wich is delayed aggro fromt eh time you cast it to the time it lands. Also granted you can land 2 stuns if you are paying attention in inv. I just dont think the term instant aggro is appropriate here. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
